<section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">The Smartest Path to Scale Your Portfolio</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600">
        Compare DSCR financing against traditional income documentation and see how leverage can keep your portfolio growing.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Why Investors Use DSCR Loans</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
          DSCR loans qualify based on property income instead of personal tax returns. That means higher leverage, faster approvals, and flexibility for complex financial profiles.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
          <li class="flex"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-green-500 mr-2 mt-1" aria-hidden="true"></i>Qualify using property cash flow, not personal DTI.</li>
          <li class="flex"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-green-500 mr-2 mt-1" aria-hidden="true"></i>Close in personal name or LLC for liability management.</li>
          <li class="flex"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-green-500 mr-2 mt-1" aria-hidden="true"></i>Great for expanding short-term rental portfolios.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 md:mt-0">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Why Traditional Financing Can Fall Short</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
          Conventional underwriting often penalizes investors for write-offs, multiple properties, or LLC ownership. DSCR programs bypass those limitations while keeping terms competitive.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
          <li class="flex"><i class="fa-solid fa-xmark text-red-400 mr-2 mt-1" aria-hidden="true"></i>Requires full tax returns and W-2/1099 documentation.</li>
          <li class="flex"><i class="fa-solid fa-xmark text-red-400 mr-2 mt-1" aria-hidden="true"></i>May cap property counts or require additional reserves.</li>
          <li class="flex"><i class="fa-solid fa-xmark text-red-400 mr-2 mt-1" aria-hidden="true"></i>Harder to close under an LLC structure.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

